# Prettier ignore list.
#
# Makefiles are tab-indented by spec (GNU make requires recipe lines to begin
# with a literal TAB or it fails with "missing separator. Stop."). Prettier
# doesn't natively parse makefiles, but plugins (or accidentally running
# `prettier --write **/*`) can mangle them. Patterns below are gitignore-
# style and match at any depth.

# Makefiles
Makefile
Makefile.*
makefile
GNUmakefile
*.mk

# Build / install artifacts (not source — never useful to format)
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.venv/
.docker-stage/
.dev/
.prod/
.turbo/
.next/
.cache/

# Lockfiles — never format
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
yarn.lock
poetry.lock
uv.lock
Cargo.lock
go.sum
